column91: de bonne famille et qui a du pouvoir.»\n\nAlors que je déclarais ma volonté de vivre une vie glorieuse et glamour
column92:
mon père a décidé de faire du prince héritier mon fiancé?! Est-il fou?!

«Pourquoi évitez-vous votre engagement avec le prince héritier?»

«Parce que ça me fait peur! Il tue les gens qui ne lui obéissent pas!»

Quelques jours plus tard
column93: le prince héritier m'a envoyé une lettre.\n\n«Ne t'inquiète pas
column94:
je ne te tuerai pas.»

Oh non… ai-je déjà fait quelque chose qui valait la peine de mourir?

column16: description:{"en":"After losing his leg as a startup adventurer
column17: he retired to his hometown in the countryside. Doing things such as collecting medicinal herbs
column18: exterminating magic beasts and wild beasts
column19: and helping with the villagers’ farm work
column20: it’s hard to decide whether to call our protagonist an adventurer or a handyman. And while doing these things his age quickly approached thirty.   \n  \nOne day while searching the mountains for herbs
column21: he discovered an abandoned child. Thinking that he couldn’t just leave it
column22: he took it home and raised it until his age approached forty. His now grown-up daughter had also wanted to become an adventurer
column23: likely from growing up watching her father. Although her father had taught her the sword since she was young for self-defense
column24: her talent at it was quite impressive. Thinking that it would be better for her not to be stuck out in the country for the rest of her life
column25: our protagonist sent her to the adventurers’ guild in the Capital. His daughter officially became an adventurer.   \n  \nAfter another five years
column28: is still acting as a pseudo-adventurer in the countryside. However his daughter is now a distinguished S Class adventurer but hasn’t returned home once yet… “Just when will I get to see Daddy again…!?”"
